* Iron Raptor leaned back against the wall and looked over the damaged 
warrior, wondering just how long it would be until they saw any signs of 
life.
She looked up when she heard Prowl's voice, right beside her. Her sullen 
expression slightly lifting, a slight twinkle coming into her eyes.*

" Nothing much..."

* But then her sentence was cut off when she suddenly felt that extremely 
sharp pain in her chest flair up again. Hoping that it would never come 
back.
Iron Raptors breath stopped quickly as she leaned against the wall, hissing 
through her teeth and cluched at her spark cavity.
The pain wasn't as bad as before, but it was still enough to make her pale.*
